  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "What are Mapped Types?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Mapped types allow you to create new types by transforming properties of an existing type using iteration."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Basic Syntax"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "typescript",
      "value": "type User = {\n  name: string;\n  age: number;\n};\n\ntype ReadonlyUser = {\n  [K in keyof User]: User[K];\n};"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Using Modifiers"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "typescript",
      "value": "type PartialUser = {\n  [K in keyof User]?: User[K];\n};"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Readonly Mapped Type"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "typescript",
      "value": "type ReadonlyUser = {\n  readonly [K in keyof User]: User[K];\n};"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Remove Modifiers"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "typescript",
      "value": "type Mutable<T> = {\n  -readonly [K in keyof T]: T[K];\n};"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Mapped Types with Generics"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "typescript",
      "value": "type Nullable<T> = {\n  [K in keyof T]: T[K] | null;\n};"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Relation with Utility Types"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Utility types like Partial, Required, and Readonly are built using mapped types."
    },
    {
